    "content": "nullManage Your Quotes with CPQ\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Quotes with CPQ\n Salesforce CPQ Patch Notes\n Getting Started with Salesforce CPQ\n CPQ Products\n Types of Products\n Product Bundles\n Create a Bundle\n Add Bundle-Specific Field Sets\n Feature Guidelines\n Product Options\n Product Option Fields\n Considerations for Product Options\n Global Attributes\n Constraint Guidelines\n Configuration Attribute Guidelines\n Guidelines and Considerations for Using Nested Bundles\n Unique Quote Line Codes Based on Bundle Configuration\n Show Bundle Components on the Quote Line\n MDQ Products\n Subscription Products\n Usage-Based Products\n Add Images to Product Records\n Product Pricing Methods\n Summary Variables\n CPQ Product Fields\n Create and Edit CPQ Quotes\n Send Your CPQ Quotes\n Advanced Approvals\n Manage Your CPQ Orders\n Manage Your Subscriptions and Assets\n Amend Your Contracts and Assets\n Renew Your Contracts and Assets\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce CPQ\n Explore CPQ Solution Kits\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE CPQ\nProduct Options\n\nProduct options are individual products that users can select from when configuring a bundle.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce CPQ Editions\nProduct Option Fields\nTo create or modify a price action, enter the information in the appropriate fields. Some fields aren’t visible or editable depending on the page layout and field-level security settings.\nConsiderations for Product Options\nKeep these considerations in mind when you’re working with product options.\nGlobal Attributes\nCreate a set of configuration attributes so that users can quickly assign the attributes to any number of product options. Each configuration attribute set is shown in a collapsible drawer below each product option in the configurator. This feature reduces the time spent creating product options if your options share some of the same attributes.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
